memberdef.name: FNC_RETURN
memberdef.initializer: (0xFEFFFFFFUL) /* bit [0] ignored when processing a branch */

memberdef.name: EXC_RETURN_PREFIX
memberdef.initializer: (0xFF000000UL) /* bits [31:24] set to indicate an EXC_RETURN value */

memberdef.name: EXC_RETURN_S
memberdef.initializer: (0x00000040UL) /* bit [6] stack used to push registers: 0=Non-secure 1=Secure */

memberdef.name: EXC_RETURN_DCRS
memberdef.initializer: (0x00000020UL) /* bit [5] stacking rules for called registers: 0=skipped 1=saved */

memberdef.name: EXC_RETURN_FTYPE
memberdef.initializer: (0x00000010UL) /* bit [4] allocate stack for floating-point context: 0=done 1=skipped */

memberdef.name: EXC_RETURN_MODE
memberdef.initializer: (0x00000008UL) /* bit [3] processor mode for return: 0=Handler mode 1=Thread mode */

memberdef.name: EXC_RETURN_SPSEL
memberdef.initializer: (0x00000004UL) /* bit [2] stack pointer used to restore context: 0=MSP 1=PSP */

memberdef.name: EXC_RETURN_ES
memberdef.initializer: (0x00000001UL) /* bit [0] security state exception was taken to: 0=Non-secure 1=Secure */

memberdef.name: EXC_INTEGRITY_SIGNATURE
memberdef.initializer: (0xFEFA125BUL) /* Value for processors without floating-point extension */
